        <node id="1093" version="06afcf8f-aa44-475b-9d66-7ff0427ccb87" parentID="1092" level="3" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1090" template="1091" sortOrder="1" createDate="2009-01-08T14:25:12" updateDate="2009-01-26T15:40:02" nodeName="Functionality" urlName="functionality" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqCategory" path="-1,1047,1092,1093">
          <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>Questions about the functionality of this Runway module.</p>]]></data>
          <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
          <data alias="ShowForm">1</data>
          <node id="1109" version="c026b421-2e96-4a5b-a878-cac67e9e24bf" parentID="1093" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1088" template="1099" sortOrder="2" createDate="2009-01-09T12:48:36" updateDate="2009-01-26T15:40:02" nodeName="Look &amp; Feel" urlName="look--feel" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqQuestion" path="-1,1047,1092,1093,1109">
            <data alias="questionText"><![CDATA[<p>Can I change the looks of this module?</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>Yes, this module includes a separate CSS file, especially for the look and feel of this module. Take a look in the settings section, under Stylesheets you can find a file called umbracoFAQ.css.</p>
<p>There you can edit all looks for the categories, questions, and the form to submit a question.</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
          </node>
          <node id="1110" version="f1db6028-ca94-46e0-8d7b-1f42dfc8e7ff" parentID="1093" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1088" template="1099" sortOrder="3" createDate="2009-01-09T12:49:15" updateDate="2009-01-26T15:40:02" nodeName="Submit a question" urlName="submit-a-question" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqQuestion" path="-1,1047,1092,1093,1110">
            <data alias="questionText"><![CDATA[<p>Can I let my users suggest certain questions?</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>Yes that is possible, there is a form to give your users the opportunity to submit questions.</p>
<p>You cannot use the form on pages other than the FAQ or a specific Category in the FAQ, this is made so to prevent Question nodes to be appended to unsupported places in your site.</p>
<p>You can disable the form for each category in the properties of a category on in the <strong>content </strong>section.</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
          </node>
          <node id="1111" version="d7e4cf28-0f54-4da8-8082-aa43436205fd" parentID="1093" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1088" template="1099" sortOrder="4" createDate="2009-01-09T12:49:57" updateDate="2009-01-26T15:40:02" nodeName="Change functionality" urlName="change-functionality" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqQuestion" path="-1,1047,1092,1093,1111">
            <data alias="questionText"><![CDATA[<p>I would like to change the functionality of this module, where and how do I start?</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>Well, there are 2 places you need to be,</p>
<ol>
<li>to change the functionality of the lists (category listing or question listing)<br />you can do that in the <strong>developer section</strong> in the umbraco backend, under <strong>XSLT Files</strong> you will find 2 files called <strong>Faq List Categories</strong> &amp; <strong>Faq List Questions</strong>.</li>
<li>to change the functionality of the form (submit a question form)<br />you will need to dig a little bit deeper, this form is a custom build user control which you will find the control (<strong>AddFaqQuestion.ascx</strong>) in the <strong>usercontrols </strong>directory of your umbraco installation. <br />And the codebehind (<strong>AddFaqQuestion.ascx.cs</strong>) and designer file (<strong>AddFaqQuestion.ascx.designer.cs</strong>) in the <strong>app_code/Umbraco.NitroFAQ</strong> directory of your umbraco installation.</li>
</ol>]]></data>
            <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
          </node>
          <node id="1112" version="2b195319-1c6a-4757-9cce-34ac8a28176c" parentID="1093" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1088" template="1099" sortOrder="5" createDate="2009-01-09T13:45:35" updateDate="2009-01-26T15:40:02" nodeName="Hide from navigation" urlName="hide-from-navigation" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqQuestion" path="-1,1047,1092,1093,1112">
            <data alias="questionText"><![CDATA[<p>Can I hide questions or categories from the navigation or sitemap?</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>Yes, the umbracoNaviHide property is added in the properties so you can choose to hide certain questions or categories from an automatically generated menu or site map.</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
          </node>
          <node id="1107" version="160434c6-022f-447c-bf21-d23597cdde19" parentID="1093" level="4" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1088" template="1099" sortOrder="9" createDate="2009-01-09T12:17:16" updateDate="2009-01-26T15:40:02" nodeName="Categories" urlName="categories" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqQuestion" path="-1,1047,1092,1093,1107">
            <data alias="questionText"><![CDATA[<p>Can this FAQ module use categories?</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>Yes it most certainly can.<br />It supports categories and just a single list of questions.</p>
<p>In the content section you can add a new category under the FAQ node.</p>
<p>However, you do not need to add categories. If you want just a simple FAQ on your website with only a few questions you can add them directly under the FAQ page.</p>]]></data>
            <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
          </node>
        </node>
        <node id="1108" version="77f510f9-c10e-4da6-8750-919969837fb6" parentID="1092" level="3" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1088" template="1099" sortOrder="2" createDate="2009-01-09T12:47:39" updateDate="2009-01-20T17:09:54" nodeName="What is this Runway module?" urlName="what-is-this-runway-module" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqQuestion" path="-1,1047,1092,1108">
          <data alias="questionText"><![CDATA[<p>What is this Runway module?</p>]]></data>
          <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>This is a simple FAQ module created for Runway.</p>
<p>You can read all about what it can and cannot do in the category <strong>Functionality</strong>.</p>]]></data>
          <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
        </node>
        <node id="1113" version="bb3b3c33-494f-496a-9c06-e3df625b76e4" parentID="1092" level="3" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1088" template="1099" sortOrder="3" createDate="2009-01-09T14:52:46" updateDate="2009-01-20T17:09:54" nodeName="You have other questions? " urlName="you-have-other-questions-" writerName="Administrator" creatorName="Administrator" nodeTypeAlias="faqQuestion" path="-1,1047,1092,1113">
          <data alias="questionText"><![CDATA[<p>You have other questions?</p>]]></data>
          <data alias="bodyText"><![CDATA[<p>If you still&nbsp;have - after reading all the faqs - other questions, we - at <a href="http://www.netcentric.be">Netcentric </a>- will be glad to help. Sander Houtterkier (<a href="mailto:sander@netcentric.be">sander@netcentric.be</a>) and Gerty Engrie (<a href="mailto:gerty@netcentric.be">gerty@netcentric.be</a>).</p>]]></data>
          <data alias="umbracoNaviHide">0</data>
        </node>
